question:
The thickness of a steel sheet follows a uniform distribution with values between 150 and 200 millimeters. Suppose we perform the following experiment over and over again: Randomly sample 11 steel sheets from the production line and record the thickness, $x$, of each. Calculate the two sample statistics

$$
\begin{aligned}
\bar{x}= & \text { Sample mean }=\frac{\Sigma x}{11} \\
m= & \text { Median }=\begin{array}{l}
\text { Sixth sample measurement when the } 11 \text { thicknesses } \\
\\
\\
\text { are arranged in ascending order }
\end{array}
\end{aligned}
$$


Obtain approximations to the sampling distributions of $\bar{x}$ and $m$.
